&lt;p&gt;BlinkRx is scaling a large hourly Operations workforce across fulfillment, pharmacy, and patient support functions. The Employee Relations Partner is a dedicated specialist who owns the day-to-day employee relations work for this population, partnering closely with the Sr. HRBP, Operations leaders, and Employment Counsel to resolve issues fairly, consistently, and in line with legal requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role for someone who is comfortable owning complex cases end to end, coaching frontline managers, and operating with strong judgment in a fast-moving, multi-site environment. You will help build and strengthen the employee relations infrastructure as the organization grows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Relations, Investigations, and Case Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct timely, thorough, and well-documented workplace investigations into concerns such as misconduct, harassment, policy violations, and interpersonal conflict.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage cases end to end in HR Acuity, maintaining consistent naming conventions, clean documentation, and accurate case records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HRBPs and employment counsel on sensitive or higher-risk matters before action is taken, and escalate appropriately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and flag legal exposure (ADA, FMLA, PWFA, and related areas) before action is taken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare investigation summaries, findings, and recommended outcomes that are defensible and consistently applied.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track case trends and surface insights to the Senior HRBP to inform proactive interventions and policy updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manager Coaching and Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to frontline and operations managers, building their capability to handle routine employee relations matters independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, practical guidance grounded in policy and law, and translate complex requirements into actionable steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise managers on progressive discipline, performance concerns, and policy administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and review corrective action documents, ensuring accuracy, consistency, and risk review where appropriate.&lt;/li

