&lt;p&gt;The Operational Excellence Manager (Pharmacy Operations) is part of Blink’s Patient Services Operations team, which leads our mission to make prescriptions more affordable and deliver the best patient experience. Reporting under the Operational Excellence umbrella, this role drives process improvement, standardization, and efficiency across Hub Pharmacy Operations. You’ll partner cross-functionally with Patient Services Operations, Product &amp;amp; Engineering and Data to identify inefficiencies, streamline workflows, and execute initiatives that enhance scalability, quality, and patient impact. The ideal candidate is both a strategic thinker and hands-on executor, skilled at translating operational needs into scalable processes, tools, and data-driven insights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This will be a hybrid position based within our Pittsburgh or New York City office.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Operational Design: Drive initiatives that improve pharmacy operational efficiency, quality, and scalability. Identify bottlenecks, redundancies, and automation opportunities. Document end-to-end workflows and partner with Product and Engineering to implement process enhancements into the product platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Execution &amp;amp; Cross-Functional Collaboration: Lead cross-functional initiatives from concept through delivery, ensuring timely execution and alignment with organizational goals. Translate business needs into actionable plans and support the rollout of new workflows, offerings, and features. Build consensus, track progress, and maintain clear communication across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytics &amp;amp; Reporting: Use data to guide decisions and measure the impact of operational initiatives. Develop key performance metrics, analyze trends, and conduct root-cause analysis on performance gaps. Collaborate with the team analyst to build dashboards and share insights that drive continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational Excellence: Foster a culture of operational excellence through standardized documentation, clear metrics, and continuous improvement. Define and demonstrate what “good” looks like, driving adoption of best practices across Pharmacy Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
